Petkim, Sabanci Holding, TEB, Turkcell: Turkey Stock Preview

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-08-12T06:07:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/petkim-sabanci-holding-teb-turkcell-turkey-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in  Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 Index (XU100)  climbed 1,709.39,
or 3.4 percent, to 52,017.02 yesterday, its biggest advance
since May 2010.  Petkim Petrokimiya Holding AS (PETKM TI): Turkey’s biggest
chemicals maker said second-quarter earnings dropped to 30.8
million liras ($17 million) from 44.5 million liras the previous
year, according to a statement after the market closed. The
shares had surged 21 kurus, or 10 percent, to 2.22 liras.  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  : The diversified
holding with interests in finance, energy and media was the
largest mover by index points yesterday after surging by the
maximum permitted for the session in the final minutes of
trading. The shares jumped 58 kurus, or 11 percent, to 5.84
liras.  Turkiye Ekonomi Bankasi AS (TEBNK TI): The bank owned by
BNP Paribas AS said profit in the second quarter dropped to 30.7
million liras from 46.4 million the previous year, according to
a statement made after the close. TEB rose 4 kurus, or 2.2
percent, to 1.84 liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Turkey’s
largest mobile phone company and its largest shareholder,
 Sweden ’s  TeliaSonera AB (TLSN) , failed to resolve a dispute over
corporate governance at a special board meeting yesterday.
TeliaSonera said its rights were violated, and the sides failed
to approve a proposed dividend of 75 percent of net income for
last year or to approve financial statements from 2010. Turkcell
shares rose 10 kurus, or 1.3 percent, to 8.04 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
